'''"-eşti"''' is a widespread [[Romanian language|Romanian]] suffix used indicating a placename, being in fact a plural of the possesive suffix "[[-escu]]", used for family names. An obsolete form is "-esci" or "-eşci", being sometimes used before the beginning [[20th century]]. In some areas in Romania, more than half of the placenames have this suffix.
